29 SECTION 6.1. If Mecklenburg County creates a metropolitan public transportation
30 authority under Article 34 of Chapter 160A of the General Statutes, as enacted by Part V of this
31 act, then that Authority is subject to all of the provisions of this Part.
32 SECTION 6.2. The Authority shall conduct a study of the issues listed in this section.
33 The Authority may use any source of funding available to it to conduct the studies required by
34 this section. This specifically includes funds provided to the Authority by another unit of
35 government and funds that the Authority receives as a donation or grant from any other public or
36 private source. The Authority shall complete the study required under this section and publish a
37 report no later than July 1, 2025. The Authority shall publish the report and submit copies of the
38 report to the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, the Speaker of the House of Representatives,
39 the Legislative Library, the Mecklenburg County Board of Commissioners, the Charlotte City
40 Council, the Town of Cornelius Board of Commissioners, the Town of Davidson Board of
41 Commissioners, the Town of Huntersville Board of Commissioners, the Town of Matthews
42 Board of Commissioners, the Town of Mint Hill Board of Commissioners, the Town of
43 Mooresville Board of Commissioners, and the Pineville Town Council. The Authority shall study
44 the following issues:
45 (1) Legal and financial considerations with respect to the transfer or use of assets
46 from the City of Charlotte or the Charlotte Area Transportation System
47 (CATS) to the Authority.
48 (2) Legal and financial considerations with respect to outstanding indebtedness
49 issued by the City of Charlotte with respect to CATS to ensure no adverse
50 impacts in relation to the outstanding indebtedness.
