49 SECTION 7.1. The definitions in G.S. 159-81 apply in this Part.
50 SECTION 7.2. In addition to the revenues included in G.S. 159-81(4), a
51 municipality may include as revenues the receipts from any sales and use tax or other local tax
Senate Bill 584-First Edition Page 15

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 received by a municipality in connection with its ownership and operation of a revenue bond
2 project or a utility or public service enterprise facility or system of which a revenue bond project
3 is a part as long as the pledge of such receipts does not constitute a pledge of the municipality's
4 taxing power.
5 SECTION 7.3. In addition to the powers provided in G.S. 159-83, a municipality
6 has the authority to finance and refinance the cost of public transportation systems, facilities, or
7 equipment with bonds or notes secured in one or more of the following ways: (i) by the revenues
8 of the public transportation systems, facilities, or equipment, (ii) by pledge, mortgage, or grant
9 of a security interest in all or a portion of the real and personal property, whether owned or leased,
10 comprising the public transportation systems, facilities, or equipment, and (iii) as otherwise
11 provided in Article 5 of Chapter 159 of the General Statutes. Notwithstanding anything in
12 G.S. 159-83(a) or otherwise in Article 5 of Chapter 159 of the General Statutes to the contrary,
13 each municipality may secure bonds or notes by a pledge of all or any portion of the revenues of
14 public transportation systems, facilities, or equipment without regard to meeting the expense and
15 maintenance and operation of and renewals and replacements with respect to the revenue bond
16 project.
17 SECTION 7.4. This Part applies only to cities with a population of greater than
18 870,000 according to the 2020 federal decennial census or any subsequent federal decennial
19 census and metropolitan public transportation authorities created under Article 34 of Chapter
20 160A of the General Statutes, as enacted by Part V of this act.
