22 "(e) Each sanitary district, mosquito control district, hospital district, merged school
23 administrative unit described in G.S. 115C-513, metropolitan sewerage district, metropolitan
24 water district, metropolitan water and sewerage district, county water and sewer district, regional
25 public transportation authority, metropolitan public transportation authority, and special airport
26 district may borrow money and issue its bonds under this Article in evidence thereof for the
27 purpose of paying any capital costs of any one or more of the purposes for which it is authorized,
28 by general laws uniformly applicable throughout the State, to raise or appropriate money, except
29 for current expenses."
30 SECTION 8.9. G.S. 159-81 reads as rewritten:
31 "§ 159-81. Definitions.
32 The words and phrases defined in this section shall have the meanings indicated when used
33 in this Article:
34 (1) "Municipality" means a county, city, town, incorporated village, sanitary
35 district, metropolitan sewerage district, metropolitan water district,
36 metropolitan water and sewerage district, county water and sewer district,
37 water and sewer authority, hospital authority, hospital district, parking
38 authority, special airport district, special district created under Article 43 of
39 Chapter 105 of the General Statutes, regional public transportation authority,
40 regional transportation authority, metropolitan public transportation authority,
41 regional natural gas district, regional sports authority, airport authority, joint
42 agency created pursuant to Part 1 of Article 20 of Chapter 160A of the General
43 Statutes, a joint agency authorized by agreement between two cities to operate
44 an airport pursuant to G.S. 63-56, the North Carolina Turnpike Authority
45 described in Article 6H of Chapter 136 of the General Statutes and transferred
46 to the Department of Transportation pursuant to G.S. 136-89.182(b), and a
47 Ferry Transportation Authority created pursuant to Article 29 of Chapter
48 160A of the General Statutes, but not any other forms of State or local
49 government.
50 …."
51 SECTION 8.10. G.S. 160A-20(h) reads as rewritten:
Senate Bill 584-First Edition Page 19

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 "(h) Local Government Defined. – As used in this section, the term "unit of local
2 government" means any of the following:
3 …
4 (11) A regional public transportation authority or authority, a regional
5 transportation authority, or a metropolitan public transportation authority
6 created pursuant to Article 26 or 26, Article 27, or Article 34 of this Chapter.
7 …."
8
9 PART IX. MISCELLANEOUS PROVISIONS
10 SECTION 9.1. It is the intent of the General Assembly not to reduce transportation
11 funding allocations for any municipality in Mecklenburg County as a result of the enactment of
12 this act or the levy of a tax under the provisions of Senate Bill 145 of the 2025 General Assembly,
13 if that bill becomes law. In addition, it is the intent of the General Assembly not to reduce State
14 transportation funding for State projects located in Mecklenburg County as a result of the
15 enactment of this act or the levy of a tax under the provisions of Senate Bill 145 of the 2025
16 General Assembly, if that bill becomes law. Without specific authorization from the General
17 Assembly, the Department of Transportation may not reduce funding for any transportation
18 projects as a result of this act or the levy of a tax pursuant to the provisions of Senate Bill 145 of
19 the 2025 General Assembly, if that bill becomes law.
20 SECTION 9.2. This act becomes effective only if Senate Bill 145 of the 2025
21 General Assembly becomes law. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when Senate
22 Bill 145 of the 2025 General Assembly becomes law.
